description: From French démarquer, from New Latin *demarcō (“to mark off, set the bounds of, bound”), from Latin dē- (“off”) + Medieval Latin marcō (“to mark”), from marca (“bound, mark, march”); surface analysis de- +‎ mark. See mark, march.

verbs.description: demark (third-person singular simple present demarks, present participle demarking, simple past and past participle demarked)
